      "message": "[Medium] Line 128: 🟡 Suggestions - `bodyOverwrite` is applied after `init(msgBody, ...)` has already derived message metadata from the original body. Any body-dependent fields computed in `init` (for example emoji-only detection, preview/parsing state, or formatted content) can become inconsistent with what is actually displayed. Build the effective body before calling `init`, while preserving the original body in `commit` for editing. Suggested approach:\n```suggestion\n    auto displayBody \u003d msgBody;\n    if (auto bodyOverwriteIt \u003d msg.pluginData.find(\"bodyOverwrite\");\n        bodyOverwriteIt !\u003d msg.pluginData.end() \u0026\u0026 !bodyOverwriteIt.value().isEmpty()) {\n        displayBody[\"body\"] \u003d bodyOverwriteIt.value();\n    }\n    init(displayBody, accountUri, accountId, conversationId);\n    commit \u003d msgBody;\n```\n",
